text: My sister actually has CF and it's a constant struggle, knowing that the age expectancy for her to live until is 30/36. As I've gotten older I've realised that my little sister could one day not be with me because of something she genetically inherited by chance and that I did not. I really hope this movie does CF right as it'll have an impact around the world and on my sister, especially as she will most likely decide to go see it. I want to keep this short so to everyone out there who has CF, I'm rooting for you, you can do it and you can live your life just like anyone else would, don't let your illness restrict you. Make sure to take your medication, do your nebuliser and physio activities, remember to exercise. It's important and I want all of you to be okay. <3

text: Oh yay,  another movie that romanticizes a deadly disease. CF isn't something that pushes people together who attempt to fight fate and end up dying in each others arms saying: "well at least we got to love before we died too young." This Fault in my Stars, dying couple, romance genre thing needs to stop,  because it's bullshit.
